WEBVTT

00:05.364 --> 00:06.865
(sighs)

00:09.302 --> 00:11.304
Come on in, Monica.

00:13.706 --> 00:14.740
MONICA:
Thank you.

00:14.873 --> 00:16.375
Mm-hmm.

00:23.716 --> 00:26.352
Wow, you've known
the president a long time.

00:26.485 --> 00:29.255
Yes.
We're close.

00:29.388 --> 00:32.258
We met when we were teenagers.

00:32.391 --> 00:33.692
Oh, wow.

00:33.826 --> 00:36.829
-Closing things up here.
-Oh, sure.

00:44.737 --> 00:47.506
Okay. So...

00:47.640 --> 00:48.941
why are you here today?

00:49.074 --> 00:52.211
Oh, um, well, I applied
for the position

00:52.345 --> 00:54.613
at the National Security Office.

00:54.747 --> 00:56.315
Back here at the White House.

00:58.751 --> 01:01.387
I-I was under the impression
you were aware of that.

01:01.520 --> 01:04.623
Yes. Is there something
you'd like me to do about it?

01:04.757 --> 01:07.693
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm a little confused.

01:07.826 --> 01:11.464
I was told you were working
on placing me back here.

01:11.597 --> 01:13.031
Placing you in the White House?

01:14.367 --> 01:15.534
This is the first
I'm hearing of that.

01:15.668 --> 01:17.970
Oh.

01:18.103 --> 01:19.138
Remind me, where are you now?

01:19.272 --> 01:21.374
The Pentagon,
uh, Public Affairs.

01:21.507 --> 01:23.976
I'm the confidential assistant
to Ken Bacon,

01:24.109 --> 01:25.144
but before that, I was here.

01:25.278 --> 01:26.812
Why did you transfer out?

01:26.945 --> 01:31.750
Oh, um...
it wasn't really my decision.

01:31.884 --> 01:33.586
Whose decision was it?

01:33.719 --> 01:37.590
Evelyn Lieberman
made that arrangement.

01:37.723 --> 01:39.492
Right.

01:39.625 --> 01:41.160
I spoke to Evelyn about you.

01:41.294 --> 01:45.097
Oh, s-so you did speak
to someone?

01:45.231 --> 01:47.566
She gave me a rundown
of your departure.

01:49.635 --> 01:51.404
Monica...

01:51.537 --> 01:53.239
you've got a good job.

01:53.372 --> 01:55.674
You get to travel the world
with DoD.

01:55.808 --> 01:57.610
Why would you want
to come back here?

01:57.743 --> 02:00.446
I really love working
in the executive branch.

02:00.579 --> 02:01.647
Hmm.

02:03.148 --> 02:06.619
Well, unfortunately,

02:06.752 --> 02:08.887
that NSC job has been filled.

02:11.056 --> 02:12.858
-Oh, it has?
-Yeah.

02:12.991 --> 02:14.193
I'll just have to find
something else.

02:14.327 --> 02:17.930
Okay, um...

02:18.063 --> 02:19.865
because it's been almost a year

02:19.998 --> 02:21.200
since I was told
I'd be back here.

02:21.334 --> 02:22.501
And who told you that?

02:24.503 --> 02:25.371
He did.

02:25.504 --> 02:27.340
He who?

02:40.353 --> 02:42.187
(door opens)

02:45.023 --> 02:47.025
Linda.

02:48.093 --> 02:51.063
-Why would you do this?
-I'm not in the mood, Monica.

02:51.196 --> 02:53.232
The big creep
is gonna be so mad.

02:53.366 --> 02:57.002
Why? I called Kathleen a liar
because she is.

02:57.135 --> 02:58.837
I helped him.

02:58.971 --> 03:00.739
You said that he fondled
his employee in the West Wing.

03:00.873 --> 03:03.075
Oh, I should have known
you'd take his side.

03:03.208 --> 03:05.077
-I'm not!
-His lawyer Bob Bennett

03:05.210 --> 03:06.745
defames me on the world stage.

03:06.879 --> 03:09.415
He says I'm not
to be believed.

03:09.548 --> 03:12.518
And your only concern
is protecting him.

03:12.651 --> 03:15.254
Linda, he knows that
you and I are friends.

03:15.388 --> 03:16.589
You have to fix this.

03:16.722 --> 03:18.090
I am not the catalyst here.

03:18.223 --> 03:20.926
I didn't ask for a front-row
ticket to his misbehavior.

03:21.059 --> 03:23.929
I was handed one, forced
against my will to watch.

03:24.062 --> 03:26.765
Please. I am so close
to getting my job back.

03:26.899 --> 03:28.100
If the White House has
any excuse...

03:28.233 --> 03:30.202
I am at war
with the White House.

03:30.336 --> 03:33.272
For 20 years I have given
everything to this system.

03:33.406 --> 03:34.607
I have been nothing but loyal,

03:34.740 --> 03:36.208
and now I'm a target.

03:36.342 --> 03:38.377
I really don't think
you're a target.

03:38.511 --> 03:41.614
I was the last person
to see Vince Foster alive.

03:41.747 --> 03:45.918
The White House disposed of me
like a piece of trash.

03:47.320 --> 03:48.787
And they will do the same
to you, Monica.

03:48.921 --> 03:51.624
-I don't think so.
-Oh, trust me.

03:51.757 --> 03:53.058
I wasn't welcome back,
and you won't be either.

03:53.191 --> 03:55.260
Oh, Jesus, Linda,
no one wanted you back.

03:58.364 --> 04:00.366
(sighs)

04:00.499 --> 04:02.067
I'm sorry, I...

04:02.200 --> 04:04.136
That's not what I...

04:04.269 --> 04:05.438
That came out wrong, Linda.

04:06.439 --> 04:08.807
Linda, I am very scared,
and I'm worried about you

04:08.941 --> 04:10.242
because you're
a political appointee,

04:10.376 --> 04:12.611
-and you could lose
your job for this.
-Yeah.

04:13.612 --> 04:16.148
And then I'll write
a tell-all book.

04:16.281 --> 04:17.616
See how they like that.

04:18.617 --> 04:19.952
What does that mean?

04:21.520 --> 04:23.656
Don't be such a narcissist.

04:23.789 --> 04:27.560
It'll be about me, not you.

04:29.027 --> 04:30.796
(Monica huffs)

04:50.315 --> 04:52.317
Who left this here?

04:57.390 --> 04:59.492
Who put this here?!

05:17.175 --> 05:19.177
*

05:41.934 --> 05:44.336
(phone line ringing)

05:46.204 --> 05:48.407
LUCIANNE (on recording):
You've reached the office
of Lucianne Goldberg.

05:48.541 --> 05:49.975
-Start talking.
-(beep)

05:50.108 --> 05:52.010
Lucianne, it's Linda Tripp.

05:52.144 --> 05:53.412
I'm sure you've seen Newsweek.

05:53.546 --> 05:56.314
(sighs)
I need to talk.

05:56.449 --> 05:58.417
It's urgent, and I didn't know
who else to call.

05:58.551 --> 06:00.753
NEWSCASTER:
The pictures, for which
a London tabloid

06:00.886 --> 06:03.922
-reportedly paid $400,000...
-(phone rings)

06:04.056 --> 06:05.090
show Diana cavorting about...

06:05.223 --> 06:06.892
-Hello?
-MONICA: Hi.

06:08.827 --> 06:10.596
Hi.

06:10.729 --> 06:13.766
I just want to say again
I'm sorry about earlier.

06:13.899 --> 06:15.601
You know how important
you are to me, I just--

06:15.734 --> 06:17.102
I'm scared that
the big creep would be mad,

06:17.235 --> 06:18.270
and you and I would end up

06:18.403 --> 06:20.706
jobless in a ditch somewhere.

06:20.839 --> 06:22.274
Just kidding
about the ditch part.

06:22.407 --> 06:24.610
I understand.

06:24.743 --> 06:26.011
Do you forgive me?

06:26.144 --> 06:27.279
Of course.

06:27.412 --> 06:29.448
I have to say this has been

06:29.582 --> 06:31.950
such an unsettling 24 hours.

06:32.084 --> 06:33.786
Ugh, I know. Me, too.

06:33.919 --> 06:35.120
You know, I finally had
a meeting with Marsha.

06:35.253 --> 06:37.289
Did I tell you that?

06:37.422 --> 06:39.391
Who, I'll remind you, in July
said that there would be

06:39.525 --> 06:40.759
a job available for me
this fall

06:40.893 --> 06:43.061
and is now saying there might
not be one available

06:43.195 --> 06:45.230
-this year.
-You're kidding.

06:45.363 --> 06:47.065
No, I'm serious, Linda,
and at this point

06:47.199 --> 06:48.801
it's like Bill said
that she would secure

06:48.934 --> 06:50.903
a job for me months ago.

06:51.036 --> 06:53.972
When I call her, she acts like
she doesn't even know who I am,

06:54.106 --> 06:56.475
and then, when he
sends me back in to see her,

06:56.609 --> 06:58.911
she just sits there and stares
at me with these mean eyes

06:59.044 --> 07:01.647
and asks me all these questions,
like, "Why would you want

07:01.780 --> 07:02.981
"to come back to work
at the White House

07:03.115 --> 07:03.982
"to make less than you do

07:04.116 --> 07:05.250
at the Pentagon?"

07:05.383 --> 07:07.486
And "What's your
relationship to the president?"

07:07.620 --> 07:08.921
And it's like,
we all know why she's asking.

07:09.054 --> 07:10.823
She used to be his girlfriend.

07:10.956 --> 07:12.290
Mm-hmm.

07:12.424 --> 07:14.593
So I called Betty to see
if I could talk to him,

07:14.727 --> 07:16.895
but she keeps saying
that he's busy.

07:17.029 --> 07:18.396
I'm just so frustrated, Linda.

07:18.531 --> 07:19.998
He's the president
of the United States.

07:20.132 --> 07:22.167
He should be able to snap his
fingers and make this happen.

07:22.300 --> 07:24.336
And I know he's trying,
and I know

07:24.469 --> 07:26.338
it's not like he has a lot
of free time on his hands.

07:26.471 --> 07:28.073
But anyway...

07:29.074 --> 07:31.476
(cheering, whooping)

07:43.488 --> 07:45.090
-(quiet chatter)
-(music playing)

07:45.223 --> 07:48.093
Ryan. Allison.

07:48.226 --> 07:50.362
A little help.

07:50.495 --> 07:52.364
(chatter continues)

07:52.497 --> 07:54.432
Did anyone call for me?

07:54.567 --> 07:58.436
* And show you
that I'm real... *

07:58.571 --> 08:00.706
-A human being is speaking
to you.
-No.

08:00.839 --> 08:03.375
-(phone ringing)
-I'm not a fan of your tone.

08:03.508 --> 08:04.877
ALLISON:
Mm-hmm.

08:05.010 --> 08:06.044
Flying solo. You can join me

08:06.178 --> 08:07.713
-if you want.
-Monica.

08:07.846 --> 08:09.147
Guess again, dear.

08:09.281 --> 08:12.117
-Lucianne. Hi.
-(Lucianne laughs)

08:12.250 --> 08:14.052
I wasn't sure
you'd call me back.

08:14.186 --> 08:15.554
I probably shouldn't have.

08:15.688 --> 08:17.389
You get me all hot
and bothered thinking

08:17.522 --> 08:19.391
you're sitting on something big,
and then you vanish.

08:19.524 --> 08:21.159
Let me change phones.

08:21.293 --> 08:23.228
When I say hang up...

08:23.361 --> 08:25.564
-* Return of the Mack *
-* Oh, my God *

08:25.698 --> 08:27.566
-* You know that I'll be back *
-* Here I am... *

08:27.700 --> 08:29.735
-LUCIANNE: So, why'd you call?
-LINDA: Well, I have

08:29.868 --> 08:34.406
found myself in possession of
some very sensitive information,

08:34.539 --> 08:37.409
information of major
national importance.

08:37.542 --> 08:39.945
Yes.

08:41.647 --> 08:46.919
Last year a young woman was
placed in my office. She...

08:47.052 --> 08:50.088
-Oh, I don't know
quite how to say this.
-Linda,

08:50.222 --> 08:51.924
-I'm gonna hang up.
-No, no, no.

08:52.057 --> 08:53.826
Listen, this-this woman--

08:53.959 --> 08:57.596
she has, um, taken me in
as her confidant.

08:57.730 --> 09:01.333
And it turns out
she's the girlfriend

09:01.466 --> 09:03.435
of the president
of the United States.

09:03.568 --> 09:05.437
(Lucianne laughs)

09:05.570 --> 09:08.273
You honestly needed
that much build-up to tell me

09:08.406 --> 09:10.442
Bill Clinton has
a girl on the side? (laughs)

09:10.575 --> 09:13.612
Oh, trust me.
This is not his usual routine.

09:13.746 --> 09:15.280
-I'm talking long-term.
-Let me guess.

09:15.413 --> 09:17.783
-She's made it two days.
-No.

09:17.916 --> 09:19.652
Two years.

09:22.087 --> 09:23.956
What?

09:24.089 --> 09:26.291
It's actually quite disturbing.

09:26.424 --> 09:27.793
She was 21 when it started,

09:27.926 --> 09:29.227
an intern.

09:29.361 --> 09:31.797
He went after her immediately.

09:31.930 --> 09:33.632
I-I mean,
secret sexual encounters

09:33.766 --> 09:35.467
every chance he could get.

09:35.600 --> 09:39.037
He'd take a call with the prime
minister, she'd be on her knees.

09:39.171 --> 09:41.306
So, naturally, I am concerned

09:41.439 --> 09:43.742
about this young woman's
well-being.

09:43.876 --> 09:45.477
-Naturally.
-It's awful.

09:45.610 --> 09:47.245
He's been dragging her
through hell.

09:47.379 --> 09:49.915
Has Madame X considered

09:50.048 --> 09:51.650
-coming forward?
-No.

09:51.784 --> 09:53.752
No, she's not the type.

09:53.886 --> 09:55.988
And she thinks they're in love.

09:56.121 --> 09:57.923
And what do you think?

09:58.056 --> 10:01.493
She is in pain and-and
she can't see her way out.

10:01.626 --> 10:04.930
I mean, someone needs to end
this before anyone gets hurt.

10:05.063 --> 10:06.431
You could do a book.

10:06.564 --> 10:07.766
You really think so?

10:07.900 --> 10:10.335
Are you kidding?
The head honcho breaks

10:10.468 --> 10:12.404
the presidential seal
of an intern.

10:12.537 --> 10:14.006
That's six figures easy.

10:14.139 --> 10:16.008
Say goodbye
to bureaucratic bullshit,

10:16.141 --> 10:17.609
and you'll get to be a hero.

10:17.743 --> 10:19.011
It's your chance to

10:19.144 --> 10:21.714
expose Clinton
for what he really is.

10:23.381 --> 10:25.684
-Of course, you need proof.
-I have it.

10:25.818 --> 10:28.120
And I take notes-- dates, times.
I made an Excel

10:28.253 --> 10:31.189
spreadsheet documenting
every sexual encounter.

10:31.323 --> 10:32.825
Linda, you are not enough.

10:35.093 --> 10:37.429
You need real evidence.

10:37.562 --> 10:40.032
You said you talked to her
on the phone all the time.

10:40.165 --> 10:42.600
-Yeah.
-You could tape the calls.

10:44.236 --> 10:46.271
Pe-People do that?

10:49.174 --> 10:51.276
-I-Isn't it illegal?
-Nope.

10:51.409 --> 10:52.778
Completely kosher.

10:52.911 --> 10:55.180
(sighs)

10:56.514 --> 10:58.884
It's just...

10:59.017 --> 11:00.953
if she were to find out.

11:01.086 --> 11:03.889
Dear, we have been here before.

11:04.022 --> 11:05.390
If you're doing this,
you're going to have to commit.

11:05.523 --> 11:07.659
-(sighs)
-I know you're more accustomed

11:07.793 --> 11:09.728
to secretarial tasks,

11:09.862 --> 11:13.398
but this is your shot
at the big leagues.

11:13.531 --> 11:16.735
You're either taking it,
or you're not.

11:16.869 --> 11:18.737
So...

11:18.871 --> 11:20.873
think about it, call me back.

11:36.721 --> 11:40.759
She's standing right here...
with a bag.

11:40.893 --> 11:43.929
BETTY:
You do realize you have
to arrange visits with him

11:44.062 --> 11:46.098
in advance, like everyone else.

11:46.231 --> 11:48.600
I know. I'm sorry, but I...
I looked at his schedule,

11:48.733 --> 11:50.268
so I thought that maybe he...

11:50.402 --> 11:52.670
He's watching G.I. Jane
with Chelsea,

11:52.805 --> 11:54.973
and he cannot be disturbed.

11:56.408 --> 11:59.411
Why don't you have a seat?
Catch your breath.

12:00.412 --> 12:02.380
(Monica sighs)

12:02.514 --> 12:04.382
Oh, I feel like an idiot.

12:04.516 --> 12:06.584
I told myself
I wouldn't come here.

12:07.585 --> 12:10.455
He brought this back
from Martha's Vineyard,

12:10.588 --> 12:13.091
and he wanted me
to give these to you.

12:16.494 --> 12:18.030
All this? I just...

12:18.163 --> 12:20.298
All I asked for was a T-shirt.

12:20.432 --> 12:22.801
That's very sweet.

12:22.935 --> 12:26.905
Oh, God, everything he gets me
is so ugly.

12:27.039 --> 12:30.242
(laughs) I'll just say
one word-- Arkansas.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.710
Betty, why won't he see me?

12:32.845 --> 12:34.579
I just want to talk
about transferring back here.

12:34.712 --> 12:36.414
It'll take five minutes.
If he's watching the movie, I...

12:36.548 --> 12:38.683
I didn't invent the rules.
They apply to everyone.

12:41.453 --> 12:44.256
Okay. Sorry. I'm just...

12:44.389 --> 12:46.458
I'm in a weird place right now.

12:48.793 --> 12:50.262
Has he said anything
about my job?

12:50.395 --> 12:52.430
-He's working on it.
-Okay.

12:52.564 --> 12:53.832
Because Marsha hasn't helped
at all.

12:53.966 --> 12:56.134
He's doing the best he can.

13:02.908 --> 13:04.977
(voice breaking):
Thank you for your time, Betty.

13:07.812 --> 13:09.681
(sighs)

13:09.814 --> 13:11.917
(crying)

13:17.555 --> 13:18.556
(phone rings)

13:20.258 --> 13:23.095
-Hello.
-(Monica crying)

13:23.228 --> 13:24.529
I can't take it anymore.

13:24.662 --> 13:26.631
What happened?

13:26.764 --> 13:29.534
-All I do is the same shit.
-Where are you?

13:29.667 --> 13:30.768
Do you want me to come get you?

13:30.903 --> 13:32.871
There's something wrong
with me, Linda.

13:33.005 --> 13:34.439
I went over there.

13:34.572 --> 13:36.942
I was out of my mind. I...

13:37.075 --> 13:39.878
I was watching myself
do the thing

13:40.012 --> 13:42.380
that I promised myself
I wouldn't do.

13:42.514 --> 13:45.117
-Monica.
-And I can't even get it

13:45.250 --> 13:48.120
through my fucking skull

13:48.253 --> 13:52.290
that he doesn't give a shit
about me!

13:52.424 --> 13:55.227
I al... I always do this.

13:55.360 --> 13:57.062
Where are you?

13:57.195 --> 13:59.898
He won't even see me

14:00.032 --> 14:02.734
for two fucking minutes,

14:02.867 --> 14:05.670
and I spend every minute

14:05.803 --> 14:08.573
of every day thinking about him.

14:08.706 --> 14:12.410
It's like... it's like
a bad song that I can't

14:12.544 --> 14:15.213
get out of my head, and I...

14:19.551 --> 14:21.886
I don't... I don't want
to be here.

14:23.221 --> 14:25.557
I don't want to exist.

14:28.826 --> 14:31.396
(phone ringing)

14:33.831 --> 14:35.700
-Hello.
-LINDA: It's sick.

14:35.833 --> 14:37.435
The whole thing is sick.

14:37.569 --> 14:38.870
You should hear her talk

14:39.004 --> 14:40.605
about him. (scoffs)

14:40.738 --> 14:42.440
It's excruciating.

14:42.574 --> 14:45.043
She's in so much pain
over this pig.

14:45.177 --> 14:46.611
LUCIANNE:
The poor thing.

14:46.744 --> 14:48.780
He acts like
he's some great defender

14:48.913 --> 14:52.350
-of women.
-Mr. Feminist,
Mr. Women's Rights.

14:52.484 --> 14:53.952
He's a hypocrite.

14:54.086 --> 14:56.721
He's lied to her and led her on,
and now she is...

14:56.854 --> 14:58.456
She must be losing her mind.

14:58.590 --> 14:59.958
She is.

15:00.092 --> 15:02.160
She's losing her mind.

15:03.195 --> 15:05.030
I need to come forward.

15:05.163 --> 15:07.899
You want to do a book?

15:08.033 --> 15:09.301
It's the best thing
for everyone.

15:09.434 --> 15:12.137
I couldn't agree more.

15:12.270 --> 15:13.738
Of course, you do realize,

15:13.871 --> 15:15.974
once they get their grubby
little hands on this girl,

15:16.108 --> 15:17.976
the press will destroy her.

15:18.110 --> 15:21.413
It's a tabloid moment, then
she'll move on with her life.

15:21.546 --> 15:22.747
I don't know. You should see

15:22.880 --> 15:24.249
what the Clintons do
to his women.

15:24.382 --> 15:26.151
As soon as the name gets out,

15:26.284 --> 15:28.586
they make sure
she's chopped alive.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.822
I mean, Flowers, Jones--
they make a few calls,

15:30.955 --> 15:33.325
arrange a few leaks,
and suddenly

15:33.458 --> 15:36.094
a nice girl from Bible school
is the Whore of Babylon.

15:36.228 --> 15:39.264
Well, sure. They can do that
to cocktail waitresses

15:39.397 --> 15:43.601
or trailer people,
but Monica is different.

15:43.735 --> 15:46.438
She's from Beverly Hills,
a very privileged upbringing.

15:46.571 --> 15:48.506
I mean, she-she told me
when all this began,

15:48.640 --> 15:50.642
she knew
what she was getting into.

15:51.643 --> 15:53.678
She's no victim.

